The National Black Coalition of Federal Aviation Employees (NBCFAE), Nigeria chapter has pledged to mentor 60 students across various secondary schools in Lagos state on aviation-related programs. The executives of NBCFAE at a ‘meet the media parley’ at the Murtala Muhammed International Airport Ikeja, revealed that an awareness week to bring various students together by comparing them will have essay competition on Aviation. The coalition while explaining that between May 24 and 26, 2022, children from various schools age between 11 to 17 will be tutored on Aviation carrier and will visit various places at the airport, added that most people outside aviation industry were of the view that aviation was only about flying an aircraft. According to them, the topic of the Essay competition, ‘Impact of Aviation in Economic Development in Nigeria’ which will attract a cash reward of 200 dollars and expected to be 700 words. NBCFAE, a non-profit association, representing African American and minority employees against any type of discrimination in the agency is dedicated to promoting equal employment for African Americans, female, and minority employees. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE  ‘Officials initially offered to help but when the number of able-bodied citizens at the centre increased, they left us unattended to’
